@ENDNODE

@NODE "Install" "Installation"
@TOC "MAIN"

If you use always an other version of ╗FontLook-Auto.fwź:

1. Copy ╗FontLook-Auto.fwź in your FWMacros-Drawer.



If you dont use ╗FontLook-Auto.fwź:

1. Copy ╗FontLook-Auto.fwź in your FWMacros-Drawer.

2. Start programm ╗RexxMastź.

3. Start ╗Finalwriterź.

4. Open menu "User - Other - Preferences...". 

         * "Action" - New
         * "Name of menu" - FontLook-Auto
         * "Command" - "Type" - ARexx-Script
         * "Command" - "Select" (FontLook-Auto.fw)
         * "HotKey" - Alt+F9
         * "Accept"
         * "Save"

@ENDNODE

@NODE "Benutz" "Usage"
@TOC "MAIN"

            Start the macro with the Shortcut Alt+F9.

            You have to do:

            Select if you want to have a codelist or a layout of
            a font.

            Select the screen output. (speed is 100% faster than normal.
            idea from Frank Waechter)
            
            Select a font directory.

            You can also select the perforation sign, to collect the
            prints of the fonts.

            Last, but not least, you have to select: Save, Save+Print
            or only the print output.

                                   Thats all.

@ENDNODE

